Continental Airlines Inc saidFrontier Airlines, which it bought last year, has soughtapproval from the U.S. Bankruptcy court here to pay up to 1.9mln dlrs in employee medical, dental and other benefit claimson an expedited basis.    Continental is itself owned by Texas Air Corp &lt;TEX>.    Some 1.2 mln dlrs of the claims would be paid directly toformer Frontier employees for medical expenses incurred priorto, and immediately after, Fronter filed for bankrupcty andceased operations in August last year. REUTER&#3;